<h4><span class="mw-headline" id="Effect_2">Effect</span></h4>
<p>If the player offers a Thunderstone at <a href="/wiki/Luminous_Cave" title="Luminous Cave">Luminous Cave</a> or <a href="/wiki/Luminous_Spring" title="Luminous Spring">Luminous Spring</a>, <a href="/wiki/Pikachu_(Pok%C3%A9mon)" title="Pikachu (Pokémon)">Pikachu</a> and <a href="/wiki/Eevee_(Pok%C3%A9mon)" title="Eevee (Pokémon)">Eevee</a> can be <a href="/wiki/Evolution" title="Evolution">evolved</a> into <a href="/wiki/Raichu_(Pok%C3%A9mon)" title="Raichu (Pokémon)">Raichu</a> and <a href="/wiki/Jolteon_(Pok%C3%A9mon)" title="Jolteon (Pokémon)">Jolteon</a>, respectively. This consumes the Thunderstone.
</p><p>If thrown, it will deal 1 damage (2 if <a href="/wiki/Sticky" class="mw-redirect" title="Sticky">sticky</a>). Using this item in a dungeon will consume it, with no effect.
</p>
